<HEADLINE> Egyptian Parliament Speaker Leaves for Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of the Egyptian National
Assembly Ahmed Fathi Sorour, leading a delegation, left here
today for Casablanca on a visit to Morocco.
</P>
<P>
In a departure statement, he said he would be holding talks
with Moroccan Parliament speaker and other officials on the
current outstanding Arab issues, and preparatory works for the
convocation of an Arab parliamentary conference in Cairo
initially scheduled for May.
</P>
<P>
Sorour said that his visit to Morocco was taking place at
extraordinary political circumstances.
</P>
<P>
On the role of Arab parliaments in supporting the Middle East
peace process and in confronting Israeli intransigence, he said
that Arab parliaments were playing an important role toward
national mobilization and inter-governmental cooperation to
accelerate the peace march.
</P>
<P>
With regard to Arab parliaments' role in clearing the Arab
atmosphere, Sorour said that Damascus had recently been the seat
of an inter-Arab parliamentary conference. The conference issued
several recommendations on Arab reconciliation, and the Arab
atmosphere is certainly better than before, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
