<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Up to 60 Percent of Zimbabweans Involved in Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Some 60 to 70 percent of
Zimbabweans have been involved in drug abuse at one stage or
another, according to the Social Welfare Department.
</P>
<P>
An liaison officer with the Harare Resource Center, Joseph
Jabangwe confirmed the findings when addressing members of the
Midlands Provincial Drug and Alcohol Abuse Committee at the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
He said recent studies had indicated that some 38.1 percent of
school children had experimented with cannabis or alcohol and 35
percent of people at workplaces had also taken to drugs.
</P>
<P>
He said the aim of establishing drug and alcohol abuse
committees is to teach people about the dangers of taking hard
drugs and alcohol and to create an awareness among the Zimbabwean
population.
</P>
<P>
A regional conference on drug and alcohol abuse will be
convened at Victoria Falls in Zimbabwe in August this year, he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
