<HEADLINE> Earthquake Jolts Pakistan's Baluchistan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 2 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.5 on
the Richter scale today jolted Sibi district, Baluchistan province
where a strong earthquake killed dozens of people early Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to the preliminary analysis of the Meteorological
Station in Peshawar, the earthquake occurred at 08:58 this morning
and its epicenter was about 550 kilometers southwest of Peshawar,
the provincial capital of North West Frontier province.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of casualties or damage of
property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
