<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng's Ashes Scattered into Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Ashes of beloved Comrade Deng
Xiaoping today were scattered into the vast sea of the motherland
in accordance with the wishes of Deng himself and his family.
</P>
<P>
Deng, who passed away in Beijing on February 19 at the age of
93, was cremated on February 24.
</P>
<P>
Entrusted by the central authorities, Comrade Hu Jintao and
other central leaders, Comrade Deng Xiaoping's widow Zhuo Lin and
other family members of his escorted the ashes and scattered them
into the sea, in the most simple yet most solemn manner to express
the profound mourning for and endless memory of Comrade Deng
Xiaoping, an outstanding leader who enjoyed high prestige
acknowledged by the Party, the army, and the people of all ethnic
groups across the country, a great Marxist, a great proletarian
revolutionary, statesman, military strategist and diplomat, and a
long-tested communist fighter, the chief architect of China's
socialist reforms, opening up and modernization drive, and the
founder of the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
As a thorough-going materialist, Comrade Deng Xiaoping had in
recent years told his family about his ideas of his own funeral
affairs. He had asked his family to donate his corneas to an
eyebank, give his body for medical research, and scatter his ashes
into sea when he passed away.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng's Ashes Scattered into Sea (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the morning of March 2, the Huairentang Hall in Zhongnanhai,
where Comrade Deng Xiaoping had worked for a long time during his
lifetime, was filled with a solemn silence broken only by faint
notes of the dirge, and the flag was flown at half-mast. A color
portrait of Comrade Deng Xiaoping hung on a blue curtain in the
auditorium in the hall, flanked by black and yellow silk streamers
inscribed with memorial messages.
</P>
<P>
Below the portrait sat the casket containing Comrade Deng
Xiaoping's ashes, covered by a flag of the Communist Party of
China. In front of the casket stood the wreath dedicated by
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's widow Zhuo Lin and their children. The
casket was surrounded with fresh flowers and green
cypresses. Eight armed honor guards of the People's Liberation
Army (PLA) stood solemnly to guard the casket.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the office of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's funeral
committee, Hu Jintao, Ding Guangen, Wei Jianxing, Wen Jiabao,
Zhang Wannian and Ren Jianxin, and members of the office Luo Gan,
Zeng Qinghong, Cao Zhi, Zhu Xun, Yu Yongbo, Wang Ruilin, Zhang
Quanjing, Yang Dezhong, Hu Guangbao, Zeng Jianhui, He Chunlin, Liu
Huaqiu, Jia Qinglin, Xu Guangchun and Tang Jiaxuan, along with
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's relatives, solemnly stood there in
mourning. With extremely deep grief and profound memory, they
bowed three times to the portrait of Comrade Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Then, with Deng's children carrying his portrait, the casket
and the wreath, Hu Jintao and other leaders, Deng's widow Zhuo Lin
and some relatives, and the honor guards escorted the ashes as
they slowly stepped out of the hall.
</P>
<P>
The hearse started slowly and went out of Zhongnanhai. Staff
members of the General Offices of the CPC Central Committee and
the State Council, and PLA officers and men wearing white flowers
on their chests, clustered on both sides of the driveway to bid a
tearful farewell to Comrade Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng's Ashes Scattered into Sea-3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The hearse drove into the Xijiao airport, which was decorated
with white flowers. The national flag was flown at half mast in
condolences. Amid the sound of dirge, files of Air Force officers
and men, holding their hats and wearing white flowers on their
chests, followed the aircraft carrying comrade Deng Xiaoping's
ashes with their eyes as it took off and flew out toward the sea.
</P>
<P>
Inside the cabin of the aircraft hung the portrait of comrade
Deng Xiaoping and streamers of "Eternal glory to Dear comrade Deng
Xiaoping," "Dear comrade Deng Xiaoping lives in our hearts
forever." Deng's cinerary casket was covered with the flag of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and surrounded with more streamers.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, Zhuo Lin and deng's children with zhuo, Deng Lin,
Deng Pufang, Deng Nan, Deng Rong and Deng Zhifang, full of grief
and tears, slowly cast the ashes of comrade Deng Xiaoping with
colorful flower petals over the endless blue waves of the
sea. Meanwhile, the other leaders and Deng's relatives stood in
silent tribute.
</P>
<P>
Although Comrade Deng Xiaoping has left us, he will be there
forever with the sea, the motherland and the people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
