<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Casting of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's Ashes (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Morning, March 2 of 1997, a silver
grey plane with a special mission took off from the Xijiao Airport
in west Beijing. It made a circle low and slowly over the Chinese
capital, and then penetrated the clouds and flew toward the vast
sea of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Carried on the plane were the ashes of Comrade Deng Xiaoping,
who was deeply loved and esteemed by the whole Party, the whole
army, and the people of various ethnic groups throughout the
country. The casket was covered by a bright red flag of the
Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Today, Comrade Hu Jintao and other central leaders, along with
Deng's widow Zhuo Lin and other family members, were fulfilling
the last wish of Comrade Deng Xiaoping in an utterly plain yet
solemn manner.
</P>
<P>
The plane headed for the sea, a place with which this great man
of the century had been most fascinated throughout his magnificent
life.
</P>
<P>
Even the Heaven seemed to be touched, for a splendid rainbow
emerged in the horizon when the plane was approaching the sea.
</P>
<P>
At 11:25 a.m., the plane descended to 1,800 meters. Trying hard
to hold grief, the 81-year-old, tearful Zhuo Lin took out a
handful of Deng's ashes with shaking hands.
</P>
<P>
She held the ashes in her hands for quite a long time before
letting them go down into the sea together with colorful flower
petals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
