<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Routes Lions at China Basketball Playoffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Defending Champions August First
Rockets routed Shenyang Lions 128-78 Sunday as loped-side games
were seen at the first leg matches of the quarterfinals at Chinese
basketball first division league.
</P>
<P>
The three other home teams joined the Rockets in the first
round victories celebrations as Guangdong Tigers beat Shanghai
Oriental 84-74, Shandong Fleming Bulls defeated Jiangsu Nangang
104-72 and Liaoning Hunters shot down Lianhuang Eagles 80-55.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yudong hit 27 points to lead seven Rockets players finish
in double figures. Adijiang added 22, including 6 three pointers,
to the 50-points win over the Lions, who lost their starting
center Zhao Renbin who suffered an wrist fracture tow weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Shangdong Fleming Bulls also enjoyed an easy win of 32-point
margin over Jiangsu, who lost their top gun Hu Weidong with 13
minutes and 3 points in the game.
</P>
<P>
Hu won the scoring title of the league, averagin 30.9 points in
the 22-round regular season.
</P>
<P>
Gang Xiaobin led the Fleming Bulls with 34 points while Ji
Minshang added 23 points and 14 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
Li Chuanjiang scored 22 points to lead the sharp shooting
Guangdong Tigers, who were 27 of 53 from the field while Shanghai,
26 of 61, tailed all the way after a 3-0 lead in the first two
minutes of the play.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiaoyong had 10 points, 8 assists and 4 rebounds as all the
five Hunters starters came out with double figures. The hunters
breathless defence held Lianghang Eagles top scorer Liu Tie to
just 2 points in 18 minutes. Liu led the Eagles with 23.6 points
per game this season.
</P>
<P>
The second leg of the quarterfinals will be held on next
Wednesday. With the combined scores of the two games, the winners
advence into the top four spots at the 12-team first division
League. 
</P>
</TEXT>
