<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Coming to Eternity in the Sea (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng loved the sea for his whole life. The many ups and downs
in his political life were just like the sea waves.
</P>
<P>
In his revolutionary career for over half a century, in spite
of the numerous dangers and risks he encountered, he had always
been indomitable. The more setbacks he went through, the more
vigorously he roused himself again. Time and again, he had been
able to turn the tide at crucial moment, demonstrating the
dauntless heroism of a great proletarian revolutionary.
</P>
<P>
At 11:50, the aircraft completed the task of casting Deng's
ashes and headed back.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's heart had been linked with the hearts
of the people throughout the country, of the compatriots in
Hongkong, Macao and Taiwan and of the overseas Chinese.
</P>
<P>
He would see that the great cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics he initiated will be continued with a
bright future.
</P>
<P>
The rolling waves would perhaps carry his ashes to Hong Kong
and Macao, where his concept of "one country, two systems" will
soon become a reality.
</P>
<P>
The waves would perhaps carry his ashes to Taiwan. He would see
the final reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
The waves would perhaps carry his ashes to the Pacific Ocean,
to the Indian Ocean and to the Atlantic Ocean, for he does not
only belong to China, but also to the world.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping--it is a name that will live forever in the
hearts of billions of people with eternal glory. He will come to
eternity in the sea.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Report: Coming to Eternity in the Sea (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping and Zhuo Lin met in Yan'an in August 1939 when
the latter was attending a school there. They fell in love and got
married. Deng was then 35 and Zhuo lin 23. The couple spent 58
years together, going through all the vicissitudes of life. Now,
facing the ashes of her beloved husband, how could she not be
stricken with profound grief?
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, who was also filled with sorrow, scattered slowly
the ashes and petals over the sea.
</P>
<P>
He was followed by Deng Xiaoping's five children - Deng Lin,
Deng Pufang, Deng Nan, Deng Rong and Deng Zhifang, and his four
grandchildren - Mianzi, Mengzi, Yangyang and Xiaodi, who, kneeing
in the cabin, scattered the ashes and flower petals over the sea,
fulfilling the last wish of their beloved father and grandfather.
</P>
<P>
Choking with tears, Deng Rong said, "Daddy, you have returned
to the sea, and to the nature. May you rest in peace."
</P>
<P>
Sun Yong and Zhang Baozhong had been Deng's bodyguards for many
years. In military uniforms, they were now guarding the casket as
they used to guard Deng during his lifetime.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
