<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Million-Pound U.S. Aid Bag Stolen at London Heathrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- A bag containing about 1.5 million
pounds (about 2.4 million U.S. dollars) in cash, part of an
American aid package to Russia, was stolen at Heathrow Airport in
London last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Scotland Yard was quoted by BBC television as saying earlier
today that the money disappeared from a high security compound
shortly before it was to be loaded onto a flight to Moscow after
arriving from New York.
</P>
<P>
It was one of four bags, containing a total of 10 million
dollars, in a sealed container and it was supposed to be under
constant watch by a security guard at the time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
