<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wins Dunhill Cup Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 2 (Xinhua) -- China emerged as the
champion of the Dunhill Cup soccer tournament Sunday by beating
Bosnia Herzegovina 3-0 in the final.
</P>
<P>
After a scoreless draw in the first half, China sent in fresh
legs in the second half and they pumped in three goals to keep
them unbeaten in all five outings in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
China started off aggressively and forced the Bosnians to move
deep into defence. With attacks flying in from all angles, Bosnian
goalkeeper Dedic Mirsad had to leave his position often to save
the situation.
</P>
<P>
China came fighting in the second half and subsitute Li Jinyu
ended the goal drought by scoring in the 56th minute.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinyu, who replaced Li Bing, collected a pass from Zhang
Xiaorui and tricked Mirsad to put China 1-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
Two minutes later Zhang Xiaorui, another subsitute who came in
for Peng Weiguo during the break, consolidated China's position
when he blasted in a rebound from Mirsad.
</P>
<P>
Another subsitute, Ma Mingyu, set up the third goal when he
crossed from the right flank for an unmarked Hao Haidong to head
in the ball in the 80st minute.
</P>
<P>
Bosnia tried to make a comeback but it was too late with the
Chinese keeping up the pressure and denying them any chances.
</P>
<P>
The second Dunhill Cup tournament will be held in Ho Chin Minh
City in Vietnam in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The inaugural Dunhill Cup tournament which opened on February
21 had attracted eight teams. Besides China and Bosnia, other
participating teams were Malaysia, Singapore, Finland, Indonesia,
Vietnam and Zimbabwe. enditem


nnnn
</P>
