<HEADLINE> U.S. Criticized for Attempting to Prolong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 2 (Xinhua) -- An Iraqi daily today criticized
the U.S. for attempting to prolong U.N.-imposed sanctions on Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Ath-Thawra Daily, organ of the major Arab Ba'th Socialist
Party, said U.S. "attempts to prolong the sanctions and inflict
more harm on the Iraqi people.'
</P>
<P>
The paper said that U.S. has been intending to "attack Iraq and
destroy its infrastructure, and to stop the country's scientific
progress and development."
</P>
<P>
"The time has gone when Washington used to dictate its will on
the international community, a fact that the U.S. should
understand to be able to reconsider its calculations and
priorities," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It said Iraq cooperated seriously with U.N. and the
U.N. Special Commission (UNSCOM) in charge of disarming
Iraq. "However, the cooperation has not resulted in the lifting of
the sanctions because U.S. impeded the finalization of the
UNSCOM's mission," the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
It also appealed to international community to help lift the
sanctions which were imposed six years ago for Iraq's invasion of
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Only after UNSCOM clarifies that Iraq has destroyed all the
weapons of mass destruction, can the sanctions be lifted,
according to U.N. resolutions. 
</P>
