<HEADLINE> Iranian Speaker Receives Invitation to Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Parliament Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq-Nouri will visit Russia in April as a major campaign
for Iran's 7th presidential elections scheduled for May 23,
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that the 54-year-old speaker received the official
invitation from Speaker of Russian State Duma Gennady Seleznev.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the invitation was delivered to Nateq-
Nouri by Russian Ambassador to Tehran Sergei Tretyakov here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador termed the visit to Moscow by the Iranian
parliament speaker as a major step toward strengthening
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
However, Iranian authorities said earlier that the visit by
Nateq-Nouri to Moscow has been postponed due to the likelihood
of drastic changes in the Russian government.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the Iranian parliament speaker
would prefer an earlier visit to Moscow in a bid to gain much
publicity during the trip.
</P>
<P>
Nateq-Nouri is a front-runner among the four nominees in the
current presidential race. He has a strong possibility of
winning the 7th presidential elections this year.
</P>
<P>
While stressing importance of strategic relations between the
two countries, Nateq-Nouri said consolidation of Tehran-Moscow
ties will have positive and constructive impacts on all regional
and world countries.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming visit by the strong presidential candidacy
shows that the Iranian regime attaches greater importance to its
strategic relations with its northern neighbor of Russia, which
has already sold three submarines and nuclear reactors to Iran
despite strong opposition by the United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
