<HEADLINE> 1,000 Zairean, Burundian Refugees Enter into </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 2 (Xinhua) -- An average of 1,000 Zairean
and Burundian refugees is entering Kigoma Town in western
Tanzania a day.
</P>
<P>
A senior Kigoma regional government official told the official
Daily News today over the telphone that the number will be much
higher when combined with those passing through illegal
routes.
</P>
<P>
The official said, "over 1,000 Zairean and Burundians were
recorded in Kigoma Saturday, and 600 on Fiday, and all of whom
crossed through Kaguaga, Mwangongo, Kisiga and Kasete villeges."
</P>
<P>
The official added some 1,400 refugees are being ferried every
day from the holding centers using United Nations High Commission
for Refugees trucks.
</P>
<P>
He said that about 45 trucks carrying an average of 40
refugees were yesterday ferrying Zaireans from Lake Tanganyika
Stadium to Lugufu camp, some 81 kilometers near Uvinsa Salt Mine.
enditem

=03021919

=03021926
NNNN
03:26 03:26 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
