<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-02 20:39 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tunisia, Egypt Sign Cooperative Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia and Egypt today signed nine
agreements and protocols of cooperation in the fields of energy,
transport, communications, housing and trade.
</P>
<P>
The documents were signed at the end of the three-day visit by
Egyptian Prime Minister Kamal El Ganzouri.
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed on examining the prospect of
establishing a free trade zone between the two countries and the
founding of a joint bank.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri left here this evening after co-chairing, together
with his Tunisian counterpart Hamed Karoui, the fifth session
of the joint Tunisian-Egyptian supreme committee which was devoted
to the promotion of bilateral economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri also had talks with Tunisian President Zene al-Abidine
Ben Ali.
</P>
<P>
In a departure statement, the Egyptian prime minister affirmed
that political ties between Egypt and Tunisia were excellent.
</P>
<P>
He underscored the keen interest of the two parties to double
efforts and enhance cooperation for the promotion of partnership
between a number of Arab states, including Tunisia and Egypt in
particular, and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Ganzouri also reiterated the necessity of inter-Arab
cooperation and integration, particularly now that prominent world
changes were taking place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
