<HEADLINE> South Africa to Donate Insecticide to Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, March 2 (Xinhua) -- South Africa will grant
Mozambique 20,000 liters of insecticide to help remove locusts
in its four central provinces, the Mozambique Information
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was pledged by South African's agricultural minister,
said Mozmabican Minister of Agriculture and Fishing Sergio
Gouveia today in the capital.
</P>
<P>
Gouveia noted that Mozambique needs 30,000 liters of pesticide
to kill the locusts, adding that 5,000 liters has arrived in Port
Beira and will be distributed to the locus-hit areas as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
The four Mozambican provinces -- Manica, Sofala, Niassa
and Cabo Delgado -- have been suffering from the locust plague
since mid last year, which has caused great losses to their
agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
Mozambique has been making efforts to destroy the locusts, but
made little progress. 
</P>
