<HEADLINE> Li Peng on Reform of State-Owned Enterprises (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Li urged that prominence should be given to Beijing's
characteristics in urban development in a bid to give full scope
to its advantages and favorable conditions#,so that solid
foundation can be laid for the city to serve as the national
political and cultural center.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he called on the municipal authorities to effect a
change in both economic structure and the mode of economic growth,
focus on improvement of the quality and efficiency of economic
growth, and make progress based on stability.
</P>
<P>
In view of its actual conditions, Li suggested, the capital
should focus on service industry, such as commercial and catering
trades.
</P>
<P>
He asked the municipality to take full advantage of its rich
tourism resources as an ancient capital and strive to promote both
domestic and international tourism.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, Beijing's agriculture should focus on increased
application of new technologies in agricultural production so that
better farm and sideline produce can be produced.
</P>
<P>
The premier acknowledged that Beijing should also serve as a
good example for other parts of China to follow by promoting
socialist ethical and cultural progress.
</P>
<P>
As a member deputy of the Beijing delegation, he also asked the
municipal authorities to ease the ban on the practice of setting
off fireworks in the urban area by allowing residents in several
neighborhoods to set off fireworks during national festivals.
</P>
<P>
"Especially since Hong Kong's return is in sight, and the
central authorities have decided on a grand celebration to mark
the event," said the premier.  
