<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Traffic Accident in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Six people, including four women
and two children, were killed and 77 others injured, four of them
seriously, when a truck carrying them overturned in India's Bihar
State on Sunday, the Press Trust of India reported today.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the victims were on their way to a
polling station for local elections.
</P>
<P>
