<HEADLINE> Communist Party Leader On Learning from Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, a member of the
standing committee of the CPC Central Committee's Politburo, said
today that the great banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics must be held high and the
Party's
 line and principles upheld.
</P>
<P>
All party comrades, especially leading cadres of all levels,
should be under the strong leadership of the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and should follow the will
of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
In a speech marking the opening of the Central Party School's
new semester, Hu called on the leading cadres to learn from Deng
and his way of observing both the international and domestic
situation. Deng was far-sighted and always observed the situation
scientifically, Hu noted.
</P>
<P>
"We should follow the teachings of Comrade Deng Xiaoping to
concentrate all force and wisdom on pushing the sustained, rapid
and healthy development of the national economy forward," Hu told
the participants who were teachers and students in the school.
</P>
<P>
The main task for this year is to maintain social stability and
smoothly push forward the reforms, opening up, and modernization
drive, according to Hu, who quoted Deng in pointing out that the
number one issue in China is stability.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also president of the school, called on leading cadres
throughout China to keep an open mind and to eliminate any factor
that could affect stability. He stressed the building of a
high-quality army of cadres and accelerating the anti-corruption
campaign.
</P>
<P>
The participants honored Deng with a three-minute silence at
the beginning of the opening ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
