<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Central Banker Sees No Prospect for Raising Interest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- President of the German central bank
Hans Tietmeyer today ruled out the possibility of raising key
interest rates of the country in the near future.
</P>
<P>
"For the foreseeable future, we see no turning point for an
upward correction of interest rates," Tietmeyer said.
</P>
<P>
Germany's key interest rates currently stayed fixed at post-war
record lows of 2.5 percent for the discount rate and 4.5 percent
for the Lombard rate.
</P>
<P>
Lombard rate is the ceiling at which the central bank, known as
the Bundesbank, lends to commercial banks, while the discount rate
generally is the lower rate it makes available to meet bank
liquidity needs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
