<HEADLINE> Qiao on Agriculture, Township Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Qiao Shi
today called for continued efforts to reinforce the fundmental
basis of agriculture in the national economy, and to reform
township enterprises to adapt to the market development.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), made the call when attending a group
discussion of the Zhejiang deputies of the Fifth Session of the
Eighth NPC, who were deliberating Premier Li Peng's government
work report.
</P>
<P>
"There is still a lot to do to enhance the foundation of
agriculture in the national economic development in spite of good
harvests for years running," Qiao said after hearing views and
suggestions from the deputies
</P>
<P>
The relatively good farm yields last year indicate that the
efforts to strengthen agricultural development were effective and
the weather conditions generally helpful, Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
However, he noted, the climate conditions would not be always
good yearly#,so that the vigilance must never be slackened, but
preparedness to deal with natural adversities be enhanced," he
warned.
</P>
<P>
"In a populous country like China, if fluctuations occur in
agriculture and its grain production, that would be a major
problem and the whole world would be affected," Qiao said.
</P>
<P>
"All work should be done well and meticulously, from grain
production, processing, purchase and storage," he noted, saying
that "grain procurement is especially important, for it directly
concerns the enthusiasm of farmers for grain production."
</P>
<P>
"Our policy is explicit and farmers should be made to feel it
difficult to sell surplus grain, and all related problems and
loopholes must be carefully addressed," Qiao added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of China's township or village run enterprises, Qiao
said that these enterprises have scored a rapid growth these
years.
</P>
<P>
He noted that "township and village-run enterprises are now
confronted with a new situation and some problems regarding their
adaptation to socialist market economy, and on how to stand the
test of increasingly fierce market competition, and to shift its
growth mode from being extensive to intensive, as well as on how
to conduct in-depth reform, improve their product quality and
upgrade their management."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, "It is essential to look into the development of
township enterprises and absorb good experience in this regard
from different areas," Qiao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
