<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Neo-Nazis Profit From Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Internet is being widely used by
right-wing extremists in Germany to gather information on neo-Nazi
organizations worldwide, the German media reported today.
</P>
<P>
Computer samplings on the Internet have found thousands of
contact addresses and telephone numbers of right-wing extremist
organizations, Nazi symbols and slogans, such as "Skinhead Front,"
"Storm Front," and "Aryan Crusaders," according to a report by the
German news agency DPA.
</P>
<P>
German police said a U.S.- based extremist group known as White
Aryan Resistance, which preaches white supremacy, is one of
numerous far-right organizations using the Internet to publicize
its activities.
</P>
<P>
A computer specialist was quoted by the German daily Bild as
saying that the Internet was currently being "swamped by
right-wing propaganda, above all from the U.S. and Canada."
</P>
<P>
German officials said far-right organizations in the country
were profiting from such information. They also feared that
international links among extremists might be created as a
result. 
</P>
</TEXT>
