<HEADLINE> East China Province to Hold Trade Fair in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
will hold a week-long exhibition of export-oriented products in
Jakarta, the capital of Indonesia, on April 2.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will feature more than 600 products, including
handicrafts, silk, textiles, food, light industry products, and
animal husbandry products.
</P>
<P>
The show will cover an area of over 1,000 sq m and Deputy
Provincial Governor Long Anding will lead a delegation to it.
</P>
<P>
The province will also attend trade fairs to be held in New
York in June, Seoul in July, and Istanbul in September. All the
trade fairs are sponsored by the China Council for the Promotion
of International Trade in an aim to promote Chinese products.
</P>
