<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan's Ministers of Education, Culture Sacked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev today fired Education Minister Murat Zhurinov and
Culture Minister Talgat Mamashev for abusing their power for
personal gain when deciding on the list of students to study
abroad.
</P>
<P>
In his order issued today, Nazarbayev criticized Zhurinov and
Mamashev for their failure to promote the country's culture and
education while they were in office, the Kazakhstan Telegraph
Agency (KazTGA) reported.
</P>
<P>
What's more, they sought personal gain when deciding who would
go abroad to study, thus lowering the quality of the students sent
overseas and wasting the country's education funds, KazTGA quoted
the president as saying. 
