<HEADLINE> East China Province to Improve Garbage Treatment Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A garbage treatment pool of more
than 1,000 cu m will be built in the capital city of east China's
Shandong Province this year as part of the city's plan to improve
its garbage treatment facilities.
</P>
<P>
The pool is part of the municipal garbage treatment plant,
where garbage from dumping grounds and composts will be handled to
prevent pollution. A landfill of 100,000 sq m will also be built
at the plant.
</P>
<P>
The city, which is known for its springs, produces 1,500 tons
of garbage daily, according to environment officials, and there
are 720 garbage cans around the city.
</P>
<P>
At present, the city has 60,000 cu m of garbage dumps and 3,000
cu m of garbage fermenting pools. Over 95 percent of the garbage
is treated in this way. 
</P>
</TEXT>
