<HEADLINE> Work of Preparatory Committee for HK SAR Praised by Legislator (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese legislator today praised
the Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) for its contributions to Hong Kong's return to China.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch
and a deputy to the Eighth National People's Congress, proposed
that the NPC, China's top legislature, fully affirm the work of
the preparatory committee since its establishment a year ago.
</P>
<P>
With the authorization of the NPC, the Preparatory Committee of
the HKSAR has done a great deal of beneficial and effective work
for the founding of the Hong Kong SAR, contributing positively to
the smooth transfer of Hong Kong's political power," Zhou said at
a panel discussion of the Guangdong delegation to the current NPC
session.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that in retrospect, the establishment of the
Preliminary Working Committee of the Preparatory Committee was
entirely necessary and timely, which has won both the time and
initiative for the work in preparations for the founding of the
Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Owing to a non-cooperative attitude on the Hong Kong issue by
the British side, and the unilateral implementation of its
so-called Constitutional Package, the NPC Standing Committee
decided to establish in 1993 the Preliminary Working Committee
composed of representative figures from all strata in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Since its establishment in January 1996, Zhou noted, the
preparatory committee has adopted resolutions on political,
economic, legal, and social, education, cultural and other major
issues in compliance with President Jiang Zemin's principles of
"taking ourselves as the mainstay" and "facing to the Hong Kong
people and relying on them", after repeated inquiries and adoption
of reasonable proposals from the Hong Kong people, and
accomplished the election of the first chief executive of the Hong
Kong SAR and its provisional legislative council.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Work of Preparatory Committee for HK SAR Praised by Legislator (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The election of the first chief executive and the Provisional
Legislative Council not only helps to form the basic framework for
the future SAR government, but will be advantageous to Hong Kong's
smooth transition, thus drawing widespread welcome from various
strata in Hong Kong," Zhou said.
</P>
<P>
While reviewing ups and downs since the signing of the
Sino-British Joint Declaration in 1984 and the present good
situation, he stressed the farsightedness of Deng Xiaoping's
concept of 'one country, two systems'and the importance of his
instructions on how to deal with the problems that might occur
during the transition period, and the correct leadership of the
Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and its
determination to implement a series of principles and policies
concerning the issue during a new period after Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Zhou also paid tribute to the Hong Kong people for their high
sense of responsibility and enthusiasm they have shown in
safeguarding Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, and active
support and involvement in the work of preparations for the
establishment of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
There is still much to do in the next 100 days, and the
Preparatory Committee will define the method of producing the
SAR's first legislative council.
</P>
<P>
With the first chief executive and the Provisional Council in
office, Zhou said, "we should vigorously support them in
performing their duties, in an effort to help guarantee Hong
Kong's smooth transition and safeguard its long-term prosperity
and stability."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he added, the central government has also worked out
a series of principles, which require government departments in
the interior areas to strictly follow the Basic Law of the HKSAR
when dealing with affairs concerning Hong Kong after its return,
so as to ensure the all-round implementation of the concept of
"one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Hong Kong's mutually-beneficial, cooperative ties
with the interior areas is sure to scale a new height and enter
into a new period, and the great cause of the motherland's
reunification will certainly be achieved steadily and there is a
great hope for invigorating the Chinese nation, Zhou Nan said.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
