<HEADLINE> Southeast China City Improves Infrastructure And City Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Shantou, in south China's
Guangdong province, made some progress in infrastructure and city
planning construction in 1996, investing 12.6 billion yuan (1.5
billion US dollars) in fixed assets, according to an official with
the city government.
</P>
<P>
He also said the goverment has raised four billion yuan to back
major infrastructure construction. In 1996, the first phase of two
300,000 kw units of the Huaneng Power Plant went into operation,
and the Shenzhen-Shantou expressway opened, and a railway station
went operational.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of accelerating major infrastructure construction,
the city government reinforced city construction management.
</P>
<P>
The real estate market began to pick up, with 1.42 billion yuan
in housing sales, up 21.2 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The city government has put 600 million yuan in infrastructure
construction, with 470,000 square meters of roads newly completed,
a special road for motorcycles opened, and 60,000 square meters of
grassland added.  
