<HEADLINE> Zairean War Nears Zambian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Zairean civil war is less than
140 km from the Zambian border, according to today's Zambia Daily
Mail newspaper.
</P>
<P>
It quoted unconfirmed reports as saying that the fleeing
Zairean government soldiers are heading for Zambia's Copperbelt
and Luapula provinces bordering Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean government soldiers, most of whom are heading for
Lubumbashi, 60 km from Copperbelt's border towns of Chingola and
Chililabombwe, were reportedly looting villages and towns and
selling arms to feed themselves as they run away from a rebel
advance which was at present at Kamina district of Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Fleeing Assistant District Commissioner of Kamina, Kasuka
Bundala, said at the weekend that the rebel advance coming from
the north had pushed Zaire's government forces towards the
Zambian border and it would be a matter of time before they are
forced to run into Zambia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
