<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tycoon on Hong Kong Stability and Prosperity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong tycoon Henry Ying Tung
Fok said here today that Hong Kong will play a significant
role in China's modernization process, and will have more
opportunities of development with the backing of the powerful
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Fok is attending sessions of the Eighth National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
(CPPCC) and the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC). He
is vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee, and also a
deputy to the NPC.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong to the embrace of the motherland is a
great event for Hong Kong, for the Chinese nation, and for the
whole world as well," he said at a meeting of the NPC delegation
from south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
He said that the return of Hong Kong marks the start of a new
era in Hong Kong's history.
</P>
<P>
"For Hong Kong, the age of 'Letters Patent' and 'Royal
Instructions' has come to an end, and we should by no means let
these outdated laws constrain the government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR). This is a principle of
critical importance to Hong Kong's prosperity and stability," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the election of Tung Chee-hwa as the first Chief
Executive of the HKSAR has been welcomed and accepted by people
from various circles of Hong Kong, most of whom believe that Tung
is the right choice for HKSAR's leadership.
</P>
<P>
"I personally believe that the leadership of the HKSAR is
trustworthy, and has the ability to manage Hong Kong well and
promote Hong Kong's development," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that in recent years many Hong Kong residents who had
emigrated to foreign countries have returned to the land, because
they share deep affections for Hong Kong and the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"The most important thing for us to do to maintain Hong Kong's
long-term prosperity and stability is to unite the general public
of Hong Kong, and we must be principled, reasonable, tolerant, and
able to distinguish between right and wrong while seeking unity,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said it is possible that some people can't understand some
policies of the HKSAR government for a while, but after hearing
clear and patient explanations, most of these people will
gradually understand and accept the policies.
</P>
<P>
"As for those attacking the HKSAR government with vicious
intentions, no matter how well they disguise themselves, they
will not be able to stand the test of time. Time will expose
their nature," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
