<HEADLINE> Caribbean Community Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Edwin Carrington,
secretary-general of the Caribbean Community, has sent a message
of condolence to Chinese President Jiang Zemin over the death of
Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who died on February 19 at the age of
93.
</P>
<P>
Carrington extended his sincere condolences to Deng's family
and to the government and people of the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
He noted in the message that "Deng will long be remembered for
the invaluable contribution he has made to his country and as a
man who dedicated his life to the betterment of the Chinese
people."
</P>
<P>
"Deng's presence touched the lives of all, not only in
his country, but indeed the international community," Carrington
added.
</P>
<P>
The Caribbean Community now comprises 13 countries and regions
with its headquarters stationed in Georgetown, Guyana. 
</P>
