<HEADLINE> SGS International Urges Increased Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- SGS International has called for
increased trade inspection services for independent certification
of quality and condition of goods to facilitate change of custody
between buyers and sellers in the export business.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted SGS Zambia Managing Director
Albert Stockell as saying at a seminar held here at the weekend
that the most important aspect in building export competitiveness
is the establishment of firm's reputation for delivering what it
has promised to its overseas customers.
</P>
<P>
He called on companies to maintain the same quality of goods
between the samples sent to the overseas potential customers and
the goods that are actually exported.
</P>
<P>
Export Board of Zambia (EBZ) Executive Director Mwansa Musonda
told the seminar that building export competitiveness is critical
to development of Zambia's manufacturing base.
</P>
<P>
"Today's world economy is getting integrated and quality
demanding, and calls for the ability for every exporter to stand
on their own. Our export capability is the key to penetrate the
global economy," said Musonda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
