<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second APEC Fair Due in Yantai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Overseas businessmen will flock to
Yantai, a coastal city in east China's Shandong Province, to
attend the second international fair of Asia-Pacific Economic
Cooperation, scheduled for June.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, 800 overseas businessmen from nine out of the 18
APEC member countries, including Japan, the United States, New
Zealand, Singapore, Australia, and China, have registered to come
to the fair, according to Wang Dehe, director of the organizing
committee.
</P>
<P>
Official and corporate representatives from 20 non-APEC
countries and regions, such as Europe, the Middle East and Latin
America also applied to join the gathering, he added.
</P>
<P>
He estimated that the total number of overseas participants is
expected to reach 3,000 to 5,000. There will be between 500 and
700 booths set up for the event, he said.
</P>
<P>
Yantai, one of the coastal cities which opened to overseas
investment in the 1980s, plans to introduce 1,000 cooperative
projects at the fair and achieve a trade volume of one billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
To offer better back-up services, the municipal government of
Yantai is to provide 50-80 free rooms for commercial talks. A
700-million-yuan international trade mart and a
10,000-square-meter square, due to be completed at the end of
this month, will house incoming guests.
</P>
<P>
Yantai has established close economic ties with APEC
members. Of its 2.7-billion-dollar trade volume posted last year,
85 percent was gained from APEC members. Some 90 percent of the
2.8 billion dollars of overseas investment actually used by the
city was from APEC members.
</P>
<P>
The first APEC international fair was held in Osaka, Japan in
1994, with 260 booths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
