<HEADLINE> Nanjing Having More Overseas Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, a well-known cultural and
historical city in eastern China's Jiangsu Province, received 240,000
overseas tourists last year and earned 110 million U.S. dollars
from its services.
</P>
<P>
Han Jianmin, director of Nanjing City Tourism Administration,
said that over the past few years, the city, also capital of
Jiangsu, has improved its tourism programs, enriching specific
themes ranging from sightseeing, and casual entertainment, to
folkloric research.
</P>
<P>
The city has built nine major scenic areas and some 200 tourism
sites of the city have opened to overseas tourists, he said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, the city had founded 78 travel agencies and
constructed 99 tourists hotels designed for overseas tourists,
including 35 star-rated ones.
</P>
<P>
The director predicted that the city would have more overseas
tourists this year as a result of the attractive improvement of
the city's infrastructure for tourism. 
</P>
