<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Doctors Develop New Method to Detect Myocarditis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Doctors in the city of Shanghai
have developed a new medical procedure that can guarantee the fast
and accurate detection of viral myocarditis.
</P>
<P>
Doctors around the world have been diagnosing the disease with
the use of antibodies, proteins and enzymes which are related to
the virus causing myocarditis. The detection process may take as
many as three days.
</P>
<P>
Using a chemical made from polypeptides, Chinese doctors are
now able to easily and reliably detect the disease in just one
day, according to Yang Yingzhen, a professor who has conducted the
research.
</P>
<P>
More importantly, the new method requires no complex and
expensive medical equipment, so it can be carried out in small
hospitals, said Yang Yingzhen, who works at the Zhongshan Hospital
attached to the Shanghai Medical University.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that the method is also expected to be used in the
detection of some other diseases. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
