<HEADLINE> More Competitive China Merchants Travel Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Over the past decade, the China
Merchants International Tourism Corporation has handled more than
800,000 tourists, including more than 400,000 overseas travelers.
</P>
<P>
This makes the travel company, which is directly under the
China Merchants Bureau of the Ministry of Communications, a strong
competitor that can hold its own in the tourism market against the
well-known China International Travel Service, China Travel
Service, and China Youth Travel Service.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, and He Guangwei, director-general of
the China National Tourism Administration, attended a recent
reception marking the company's tenth anniversary.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders asked travel services in the country to get
a better understanding of the successful techniques used by China
Merchants, which is known for making big profits with scaled-down
administration and its fair-minded handling of tourists.
</P>
<P>
China Merchants ranked first in per capita profit many times
over the past ten years, said Zhang Yibing, general director of
the company.
</P>
<P>
Now the company is engaged in the handling of tourists, tourism
industrial business, and hotel management, with 17 travel
agencies, solely-funded or joint-funded, in Hong Kong, Britain,
Singapore, and the Chinese mainland. In addition, it has offices
in Japan, Germany and Belgium.
</P>
<P>
China Merchants is the first Category-A travel service in the
country listed on the INTERNET, as well as one of the first
Chinese members of the Asia-Pacific Travel Association, Zhang
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
