<HEADLINE> Information Cells Set Up for Pak Train Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Special information cells have
been set up to provide first-hand information to relatives of the
passengers of the train which derailed near Khanewal this morning.
</P>
<P>
The information cells are located at several major railway
stations and their telephone numbers have been declared.
</P>
<P>
At least 50 people were killed and more than 100 others injured
when five carriages of the train skidded off the tracks outside
the rural station of Mirshah near Khanewal, northeast of Multan in
Punjab province.
</P>
<P>
Rescue operations are still going on and the death toll is
expected to rise, according to sources from the railway
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The train was heading for Pakistan's southern port city of
Karachi.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report about the actual cause of the
accident.  
