<HEADLINE> French Bank Opens Branch in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A top private sector bank in
France, Societe Generale, opened a branch in Colombo today.
</P>
<P>
Societe Generale is ranked 9th in Europe and 18th in the world.
</P>
<P>
According to sources of the new branch, the bank sees Sri
Lanka as a promising location, not in the immediate present but in
the future. When that time comes, the bank does not want to be
left out, they said.
</P>
<P>
The new bank will concentrate on the corporate sector and will
offer a wide range of banking services to corporate customers, the
sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bank which claims a well-established network in all
continents hopes to harness a wide range of skills to develop
innovative solutions to client needs, they said.
</P>
<P>
At present there are many French firms actively involved in
telecommunication, water treatment and power generation projects
in Sri Lanka. With more French companies expected to invest here
soon the bank expects more business, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
It also proposes to develop off-shore banking as it believes
there is enough potential for it in the South Asian region.
</P>
