<HEADLINE> Frenchman Arrested on Child Sex Charges in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The INTERPOL said today a
Frenchman has been arrested here for allegedly having sex with
children under 15.
</P>
<P>
The man, identified as Hennion Amedee, was arrested Friday by
the International Criminal Police Organization (ICPO-INTERPOL) at
his apartment here on charges of coercing children into
prostitution.
</P>
<P>
Head of the INTERPOL's local bureau General Skadavy Math Ly Rou
said at a press conference that Amedee, 54, has forced more than
100 Cambodian children under 15 to have sex with him since he came
to the Cambodian capital on November 15, 1995.
</P>
<P>
Seven children have testified as witnesses to the charges
against Amedee, accusing the Frenchman of repeatedly coercing them
to have oral sex with him and paying two to three U.S. dollars
apiece, the police official said.
</P>
<P>
Amedee, thin with long brush moustache, showed up at today's
conference for a while with some of his victims for photo-taking
by journalists.
</P>
<P>
The police officer said Amedee will be sent to court later
today and may be sentenced to 10 to 20 years in prison under
Cambodian laws.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia approved a legislation last year imposing fines or up
to 20 years imprisonment for those involved in kidnapping, selling
or coercing minors into prostitution.
</P>
<P>
The general added that police may arrest some other foreigners
suspected of joining Amedee in forcing children into sex. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
