<HEADLINE> Share Prices Almost Unchanged on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices moved in a narrow
range earlier in the day, but closed slightly higher on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
gained merely 0.64 points to finish at 2196.34 today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 231.04 million units, valued
at 479.05 million Singapore dollars (about 337.36 million U.S.
dollars). Declines outnumbered advances 267 to 100, while 238
other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Local fruit and vegetable producer FHTK was the most actively
traded stock as it posted a turnover of 14.83 million units. It
was followed by Ber Ind. which had 7.72 million of its shares
traded. Ossia was next with 6.97 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Bus Foreign 500 led the gainers of the day as it
rose by 25 cents to finish at 7.9 Singapore dollars. M Plantations
gained 24 cents to close at 3.48 dollars, while local property
developer City Development and Cerebos closed 20 cents higher at
14.3 and 10.3 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Thai Prime Fund was the biggest loser as
it declined by 80 cents to end at 10.2 U.S. dollars. The Overseas
Union Bank (OUB) Foreign and the United Overseas Bank (UOB)
Foreign lost 70 cents each to finish at 10.4 and 15.5 Singapore
dollars respectively. Creative 50 was 60 cents lower at 17.7
Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
