<HEADLINE> First Boeing-777 Increased Gross Weight Aircraft Delivered to Southern Airlines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines has
received its first Boeing-777-200 Increased Gross Weight (IGW)
airplane, bringing the number of GE90-powered 777-200's in its
fleet to five.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that later this year, the airline will become
the first to operate the Boeing-777 on a trans-Pacific route when
it inaugurates the 777-200 IGW non-stop service from Guangzhou to
Los Angeles, a distance of approximately 7,800 statute miles
(12,550 kilometers).
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 777-200 IGW is the newest member of the 777 family
of planes.
</P>
<P>
Based in Guangzhou, the capital of south China's Guangdong
Province, China Southern Airlines received its first 777 in
December 1995. The sixth 777 is scheduled for delivery in April.
</P>
<P>
China Southern offers more than 240 routes, including 195
domestic and 46 overseas destinations. It has 62 Boeing planes,
the largest Boeing fleet in China. 
