<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China: A Big Producer for Stone Materials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China produced 100 million sq m of
stone materials including granite, marble and terrazzo in 1996,
ranking behind Italy as the world's second-largest producer of
stone.
</P>
<P>
According to a senior official with the China Chamber of
International Commerce, production of stone materials in China has
been growing at an average annual rate of 30 percent over the past
15 years. China boasts the largest reserve of stone in the world,
with the greatest variety and vast distribution of products.
</P>
<P>
A large group of important stone quarries have been established
in the provinces of Guangdong, Fujian, Sichuan, Shandong,
Zhejiang, Hunan, Hubei, Guizhou and Yunnan.
</P>
<P>
China is well-known internationally for its granite, marble and
white marble production. Its export volume of stone topped a
record 700 million US dollars in 1996. So far, China has found
markets for its stone products in Japan, the Republic of Korea,
Germany, the United States, Russia, Thailand, Indonesia as well as
Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
With steady expansion in stone production and markets, China
has made great headway in expanding Sino-foreign cooperation in
the sector by setting up over 400 foreign-funded quarries
nationwide, which have become backbones in the sector.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang Wenbo, deputy director of the China Stone
Materials Industry Association, China has also made remarkable
progress in improving its technological equipment for stone
materials production. In recent years, the country has introduced
a large amount of advanced equipment from Italy, Germany and other
countries, which effectively boosted the development of China's
stone materials production.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, China has developed equipment which conforms
to the country's stone production requirements by drawing on
advanced foreign technology.
</P>
<P>
To date, China has set up over 100 equipment manufacturing
enterprises for stone production and has basically met the
country's needs for stone.
</P>
<P>
Starting in 1990, China has exported equipment for stone
production to Russia, Kazakhstan, Pakistan, Indonesia and
Hungary.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
