<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Smooth Return of Hong Kong beyond Any Doubt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Developments in the international
and domestic situations have made Hong Kong's return to the
motherland beyond any doubt, said Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua
News Agency Hong Kong Branch.
</P>
<P>
"All signs show that a smooth return of Hong Kong is definite,"
Zhou said in a penal discussion of the on-going Fifth Session of
the Eighth National People's Congress, China's legislature.
</P>
<P>
Colonial rule in Hong Kong will come to an end in just over 100
days and the region will return to the embrace of the motherland,
shaking off a national disgrace for one and a half centuries, he
said in the panel discussion of the delegation of Guangdong
deputies.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the confidence of Hong Kong residents in its
future has been on rise, adding that the number of Hong Kong
residents migrating overseas has been declining and those coming
back increasing over the last five years.
</P>
<P>
As many as one third of those Hong Kong people residing
overseas have returned, with still more following suit.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong People now associate Hong Kong's return and
stability more closely and they have become increasingly aware of
the Chinese Government's firm determination to carry out the 'one
country, two systems' principle," Zhou said. They hope that they
will have a more secured living environment which guarantees their
business still greater prospects at the return of Hong Kong to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Acknowleding that China's high economic growth rate is a
miracle resultant from the pursuance of the road of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics in line with Deng
Xiaoping's directives, he said that this trend of development
plays a decisive role in the development of the world situation
and will surely produce a profound and far-reaching impact on the
situation in Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
The "China factor" and the "return factor" constitute two major
reasons for the rebound of the Hong Kong economy, which has ended
a two-year cyclical correctional period and grew over 4.7 percent
last year, according to Zhou.
</P>
<P>
He dismissed forecasts of a capital flight, saying: "On the
contrary, what we see is a steady inflow of international
capital."
</P>
<P>
An announcement of the International Monetary Fund based on the
summary report done on a recent survey said that the unclear
factors over the 1997 transfer of power in Hong Kong have
basically been eliminated and Hong Kong will be more prosperous
after its return.
</P>
<P>
Judging by the developing trend of the Hong Kong economy and
the external environment, Zhou said, Hong Kong's economy this year
is expected to be better than last year.
</P>
<P>
"Now only few people doubt that the status of Hong Kong as an
international financial, trade, shipping and information center
will be further consolidated and strengthened instead of being
weakened," he said.
</P>
<P>
Various pessimistic sayings about the future of Hong Kong
spread and disseminated by some Western media have gone bankrupt
before the stark, objective reality."
</P>
<P>
He went to say that the principle of "one country, two systems"
initiated by Deng Xiaoping has struck root in people's hearts and
will soon become a reality.
</P>
<P>
"We must carry forward at Deng's behest, unite the masses of
Hong Kong residents and do a good job in matters related to Hong
Kong," Zhou Nan said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
