<HEADLINE> Two Injured in Bomb Blast at Karachi Newspaper Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The chief minister of Pakistan's
southern Sindh Province today visited the scene of a bomb blast in
a newspaper office in Karachi, in which two employees were
slightly injured, sources said.
</P>
<P>
A time-bomb went off early today in the office building of the
Urdu newspaper Qaumi Akhbar in Karachi, the Sindh capital and
Pakistan's largest city, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
No one has claimed responsibility for the incident yet.
</P>
<P>
The sources said bomb disposal experts discovered that the bomb
was a home-made device of 400 gram TNT flake with a timer.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was placed on the first floor of the building and its
impact made a 14 inch diameter hole, the sources quoted the
experts as saying. Other rooms in the building were also affected.
</P>
<P>
There were no staff in the office when the bomb exploded,
causing major damage to equipment in the room, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Local police have begun investigations into the incident.
</P>
</TEXT>
