<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Speaking Training Institute for People with Difficulties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China hopes to help more than
ten million people with speech difficulties overcome their
psychological barriers by setting up the first linguistic training
center in southwestern Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The rehabilitation institute of speech psychology, formally
established on the basis of the Chengdu Hospital for Speech
Difficulties which had cured more than 10,000 patients with speech
obstacles in the past 13 years, plans to improve those patients'
confidence and realize their speech potential, said Wang Wei, head
of the institute, who is a well-known linguist.
</P>
<P>
Speech difficulties, including common problems such as
stuttering and too much nasalization, obstruct personal
communication.
</P>
<P>
The Chengdu-based institute, Wang said, will systematically
research speech psychology and rehabilitation methods while
drawing on research discoveries in other countries.
</P>
<P>
About 100 doctors and experts, all retired from the West
China's Medical University, the United University of Sichuan and
Sichuan People's Hospital, have joined the institute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
