<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Exports Maize to Its Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia is exporting maize
to its neighbors, the local newspaper Ethiopian Herald has reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, the Ethiopian Grain Enterprise is
exporting 40,000 metric tons of maize to Kenya via Djibouti and
has planned to export an additional 77,000 mt in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The report said, a private Ethiopian firm, the Ethiopia
Amalgamated, is also exporting 20,000 mt of maize to kenya.
</P>
<P>
The European Union and the World Food Program are intending to
buy maize in Ethiopia and export it to Somalia and Kenya. the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's maize surplus is now estimated at 600,000 mt.
