<HEADLINE> East China's Province Introduces Plaster Plate Production Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Nanjing, capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province, will have a production line capable of
manufacturing 20 million square meters of plaster plate annually.
</P>
<P>
Two partners, the local Jiangsu New Construction Material
Industrial Park Development Co. and US-based International
Corp. jointly raised 30 million US dollars to import the
production line made by German Deutsche Babcock. The Chinese side
invested 30 percent of the total, while the US company funded the
rest.
</P>
<P>
Slated to go into operation in 1998, the venture, located in
the Jiangsu New Construction Material Industrial Park, is the
first of its kind in the province that meet international
standards, according to local sources.  
</P>
