<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0175 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northwest China City Regulates Real Estate Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Lanzhou municipal government
in northwest China's Gansu province has ushered in large-scale
regulation of the local real estate market, normalizing
development and enforcing legal rules, including the transfer of
land using rights, house purchase and sale, mortgage and broker
services.
</P>
<P>
The total floor space of real estates of Lanzhou has reached 48
million square meters, according to statistics, with nearly 200
enterprises and 100 brokerage organizations engaging in real
estate development and management. In 1996, the city realized a
record trade volume of 21 million yuan (2.5 million US dollars) in
real estate.
</P>
<P>
While the burgeoning real estate market has been conducive to
economic development, the market has been troubled by indefinite
regulation, and questionable trade practices.
</P>
<P>
The Lanzhou government established a real estate trade
center in last October to manage the market, and regulate
real estate brokerage.
</P>
<P>
A Lanzhou municipal official indicated that new regulation
focuses on checking of the qualifications of the organizations and
individuals engaging in real estate advertising, brokerage,
appraising and auction.
</P>
<P>
Those who are qualified will receive the "Real Estate Agent
Certificate" and "Real Estate Broker Certificate".
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Real Estate Bureau and the Administration for
Industry and Commerce have issued the "Regulation on Real Estate
Medium Service Management" and "Management of the Real Estate
Information and Advertisement" to ensure the credibility of real
estate information and advertisements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
