<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coastal City of Weihai Develops Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- With encouragement from the
government, this coastal city in east China's Shandong Province
has witnessed the burgeoning of its private economic sector.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that the registered capital of the
private companies in this beachside resort by the Bohai Sea has
reached 960 million yuan (115.6 million US dollars), 3.6 percent
of the total industrial and commercial registration.
</P>
<P>
The city, one of the 14 coastal cities in China, has five
private enterprises which each have recorded more than 10 million
yuan in registered capital.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the output value of the private sector amounted to 3.5
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
While mainly engaged in handicrafts, commerce, and catering a
few years ago, the private businesses now are diversifying their
operations, with involvement in transportation, real estate
development, consultancy, tourism, advertising, culture, education
and science.
</P>
<P>
The sector has become an important source for drawing surplus
rural and urban laborers and college graduates.
</P>
<P>
The modern enterprise mechanism has become a trend for the
sector, which has already seen the establishment of over 800
limited-liability companies. 
</P>
