<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- India continued to lead in the
world's gold consumption in 1996 when for the first time more than
500 tons of gold were consumed in the country, a six-percent
increase over 1995, The Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
