talks with Ramos on March 5.
</P>
<P>
Increased commercial interaction between the two countries by
identifying new areas and commodities for export and import would
be the main topic at the talks.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministry official said the volume of trade between
the two countries now is "at a very insignificant level" although
Bangladesh enjoys a favorable trade surplus by exporting jute
goods and some traditional items.
</P>
<P>
Ramos will leave Dhaka for Islamabad, Pakistan, on March 7.
