<HEADLINE> 32 Arrested for Firing Incident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Bangladeshi police Sunday
arrested 32 people including 13 militiamen, in connection with the
killing of five villager in a land dispute in Savar county Friday
morning, police sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
All the arrested were now in the custody of the Criminal
Investigation Department (CID) in the capital Dhaka, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
At least five people were reportedly killed and dozens injured
Friday when some militiamen opened fire on villagers at Sadhapur
village to evict people from a plot owned by an industry group.
</P>
<P>
The 13 militiamen involved in the incident were arrested by the
CID officials who visited Sadhapur village and questioned the
villagers Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Deputy Speaker Abdul Hamid said in the parliament
Sunday that the home minister should make a statement on this
firing incident.
</P>
<P>
"The incident is unfortunate. The government should thoroughly
investigate it and take legal steps against those responsible for
the incident," he said.  
