<HEADLINE> "Green Screen" To Be Built For Zhujiang River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Afforestation work has been
launched in three counties in southwest China's Guizhou Province,
marking the beginning of a big "green screen" project for the
Zhujiang (Pearl) River.
</P>
<P>
The project is the second-biggest ecological undertaking
launched by the Chinese government, following the building of
shelterbelts along the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The Zhujiang River is the third-longest river in China, and the
Zhujiang River Delta, on the lower reaches of the river, is one of
the most important economic and industrial regions of China.
</P>
<P>
The region, however, has been experiencing severe soil erosion
and degradation of the ecological environment for many years, due
to over-exploitation of the river valley.
</P>
<P>
The plan of the green project has been drawn up, and it will be
first carried out in ten counties, with a total afforestation area
of about 33 million ha. At the present stage, more than 1,000
local people plant trees here on barren mountains each day.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, similar projects are being carried out in the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region and Guangdong Province along the
middle and lower reaches of the river.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0221 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Legislator: No Problems with Soeharto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The People's Consultative Assembly
(MPR) has never considered, much less discussed, holding a special
session to assess the capability of Indonesian President Soeharto,
deputy to the house speaker Ismail Hasan Metareum said.
</P>
<P>
Metareum made the remarks Sunday in response to journalists'
question on President Soeharto's statement before prospective Haj
pilgrims in Boyolali, Central Java, last Friday, Antara News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, the president among others said that he only
implemented what had been trusted by the people to him, which were
decided through the House of Representatives (DPR).
</P>
<P>
"If I am considered unable to carry out the people's mandate,
please discharge me though the MPR's special session," Soeharto
said.
</P>
<P>
He further said he had no objection or would not maintain his
position if the people wanted him to step down provided that such
a demand be made constitutionally.
</P>
<P>
However, the president noted that he would "clobber" anyone who
tried through unconstitutional means.
</P>
<P>
Ismail said the assembly's leadership had not found any crucial
problems concerning President Soeharto's capability to carry out
his administrative and stately duties to justify bringing him
before an extraordinary session.
</P>
<P>
"We can see that President Soeharto is still in sound condition
and able to overcome various challenges. MPR sees Soeharto as able
president to carry out his duties well. And whether or not he is
ready to resume the post as president for the next term, it
depends on him," he added.
</P>
<P>
The People's Consultative Assembly comprises 500 members of the
House of Representatives and 500 representatives of various
regions, professions and mass organizations. They convene every
five years to deliberate the guidelines of state policies and
elect the president and vice president.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto became acting president in 1967 and assumed full
leadership the following year. In 1972, the People's Consultative
Assembly which was established by the 1971 general election,
elected him. So far, he has been elected five times.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia will hold general elections on May 29 this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
