<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Bus Accident in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were killed and
50 injured when a bus Sunday skidded off the highway at the town
of Mulgan in Manikganj district, some 50 kilometers northwest of
Dhaka, said reports reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The death toll could rise as rescuers looking for victims said
three more dead were seen under the damaged bus that plunged into
a 30-feet dry ditch along the Dhaka-Aricha Highway Sunday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
A fire brigade team was trying to recover the bodies and look
if there were any more people trapped under the coach.
</P>
<P>
The wounded, 20 of them in critical condition, were taken to
the Manikganj General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Injured passengers said the bus was overloaded. It was also
carrying passengers on rooftop and "moving abnormally".
</P>
<P>
However, the driver could not be traced, said the police.
</P>
</TEXT>
