<HEADLINE> Romania's Soyabean Oil Output Increases in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Romania's soyabean oil output
reached 119,000 tons in 1996, up 29 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The country's soil and climate is good for soyabean
growing. Since the 1980's, soyabean has been sown extensively in
this east European country. The soyabean-growing areas in Romania
amounted to 73,000 hectares, a 7 percent increase over 1995.
</P>
<P>
At present, Romania has six soyabean-processing factories with
a total annual capacity of 357,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
To meet the need of the industry, Romania imported imported
90,000 tons of soyabean last year, of which 71 percent came from
Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
