<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Become World's Largest Palm Oil Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia will probably become the
world's largest palm oil producer because it is continuously
expanding palm oil plantation area and growing productivity, a
senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Minister Syarifuddin Baharshah said Sunday in
Sukawaringin village, Bangunrejo, Central Lampung, that at present
Indonesia's production of palm oil has exceeded four million tons,
reports reaching here today said.
</P>
<P>
The level of productivity per hectare has increased from 1.6
tons to 2.2 tons and on large enterprise-managed plantations
productivity has even reached 5.4 tons per hectare, the minister
said.
</P>
<P>
A survey team of the Indonesian Institute of Sciences has also
come to the conclusion that Indonesia will in the future replace
Malaysia as the dominant palm oil producer and regain control of
the oil palm world market.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the area of productive oil palm plantations in
Indonesia increased to two million hectares from 1994, the survey
said.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's palm oil production also increased from four
million tons in 1994 to about 4.7 million tons in 1996 and it is
expected to increase to 7.2 million tons by the year 2000 and to
9.9 million tons by the year 2005.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
