<HEADLINE> Crimes Increase in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- A total of 594,393 criminal cases
occurred in Berlin area in 1996, up 2.3 percent over the previous
year, resulting in a financial loss of 1.9 billion Deutch marks
(about 1.1 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The police have solved 264,116 cases so far, or 44.4 percent of
the total, the local newspaper, Berliner Morgenpost, reported.
</P>
<P>
Economic offenses increased by 41.4 percent, from 10,269 in
1995 to 14,525 in 1996. certificate forgery and violent crimes
rose by 23.3 percent and 6 percent respectively, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners accounted for 33.1 percent of the 164,563 criminal
suspects put on trial.
</P>
<P>
The Berlin municipal government has called on all the city
dwellers to cooperate with the police to fight against crimes.
</P>
</TEXT>
