<HEADLINE> Myllyla Wins 50 Kilometers Classical Style Skiing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Mika Myllyla of Finland put up
his best performance of his career to take the title of the
50-kilometer classical style cross-country skiing race at the
World Nordic Ski Championships at Trondheim, Norway, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In a heavy rain, Myllyla was the last to start in a field of 87
skiers. He covered the distance in 2 hours, 16 minutes and 37.5
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Erling Jevne of Norway finished second and he was followed by
compatriot Bjorn Dahlie in the third place.
</P>
<P>
It was the best result for the 27-year-old Myllyla. His
previous best mark was a silver medal in the
50-kilometer classical in the 1994 Winter Olympics at Lillehammer.
</P>
