<HEADLINE> North China Metallurgy Industry Doing Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei Province
saw speedy development in its metallurgy industry in 1996, with
industry profits ranking second among all provinces, reaching 790
million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The sector had 24.3 billion yuan in sales and nearly 2.4
billion yuan in pre-tax profits in 1996. This success was the
result of greater efforts by the industry to develop new
technology and restructure its product mix.
</P>
<P>
The province produced more than six million tons of rolled
steel last year, nearly 10 percent more than for the previous
year. Total output of wire, ship-building steel, and seamless
steel tubing rose 38 percent over 1995 to more than 271,000 tons
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Application of new technology has helped the sector add 715
million yuan in returns by increasing output, reducing energy
consumption, and improving product mix. The province's nine steel
mills all use continuous casting technology, and have led the
country in the product in 1996. They produced more than 6.7
million tons of continuous casting billets last year. enditem

