<HEADLINE> China's Central Bank Signs Contract With Sybase Software </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China (PBC),
the country's central bank, has signed a contract worth nearly two
million US dollars with the Sybase Software Co. of the United
States, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The PBC will use the company's databank programme to
co-ordinate information among its 2,000 branches, commercial banks
and non-banking financial institutions.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jing, director of the bank's Payment, Science and
Technology Department, said that the databank will also include
the data from the state's treasury, accounting, investigation and
statistics systems.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that the new databank will help "the PBC give full
play to its role as the central bank, performing its functions of
macro-adjustment and control and financial supervision, and
promulgating as well as implementing monetary policy."
</P>
<P>
Andy Jiang, managing director of Sybase China Ltd, said that
the contract is one of the largest the US company has signed in
the Asia-Pacific region this year.
</P>
<P>
The bank's respect for intellectual property right gives Sybase
confidence to further invest and increase its business in the
country's emerging economy, Jiang said.  
</P>
