<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Fiscal Revenue Outgrows Expenditure (12) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's state revenue outgrew
expenditures last year by 18 percent to 16 percent, 736.661 versus
791.438 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The revenue was 107.2 percent of the budgeted figure, or an
increase of 112.441 billion yuan over last year.
</P>
<P>
Expenditures represented 105.7 percent of the budgeted figure,
or 109.066 billion yuan more than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Last year was the second consecutive year when growth of
China's state revenue exceeded that of state expenditures, with
the margin of growth rising to two percentage points from one
percentage point in 1995. 
</P>
