<HEADLINE> Australian Wins Freestyle Skiing Aerials Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Kirstie Marshall of Australia took
the title of the women's World Cup freestyle skiing aerials race
at Meiringen-Hasliberg, Switzerland, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Marshall, the reigning world champion, collected 179.45 points,
edging her compatriot Jacqui Cooper to the second place at
174.66. Veronica Brenner of Canada finished third at 172.87.
</P>
<P>
In the men's aerials race, Eric Bergoust of the United States
scored 235.84 points for the title. Andy Messerli of Switzerland
was far behind in the second place at 226.66 whle Jean-DAmlen
Climonet of France came third at 223.82. 
</P>
