<HEADLINE> Switzerland Edges Slovakia 3-2 in Federation Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland beat Slovakia 3-2 in
their Federation Cup World group 2 first round tie on Sunday in
Kosice, Slovakia.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Open champion Martina Hingis, 16, won both her
singles matches against Katarina Studenikova and Karina Habsudova
in straight sets and then teamed up with Patty Schnyder to beat
Habsudova and Radka Zrubakova 6-0, 6-1 in the decisive doubles.
</P>
<P>
With her performances in Kosice, her native place, Hingis
maintained her unbeaten record this year.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, currently number two in the world, will become one of
the youngest player to head the WTA rankings at the end of March
when she will take over world number one position from Germany's
Steffi Graf. 
