<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Shanghai Enterprises Experiment with Modern Management System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of enterprises
selected to experiment with a modern enterprises system in China's
industrial base of Shanghai has been increased from 140 two years
ago to 250.
</P>
<P>
State-owned property of such companies accounted for 80 percent
of the city's total. Of the enterprises, 90 percent have adopted a
corporate management system and 60 percent have set up
corporations with various kinds of investment.
</P>
<P>
State industry, commerce, construction, and farm bureaus in the
city have all transformed into companies.
</P>
<P>
Achievements were also made in the property realignment. So
far, 270 group companies have been set up in the city and
management of 231 small municipal businesses has been turned over
to smaller units.
</P>
<P>
In the past two years, the municipal court dealt with 58 cases
of bankruptcy, involving debts of four billion yuan, and 59
state-owned enterprises were annexed during the period, involving
3.6 billion yuan worth of property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
