<HEADLINE> Czechs Outplay German 3-2 in Federation Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Germany, without big shots as Steffi
Graf and Anke Huber due to injuries, lost their Federation Cup
World Group 1 match to the Czech Republic on Sunday after
suffering defeats in both reverse singles.
</P>
<P>
The results earned the Czechs a semi-final clash against the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Barbara Rittner, temporary German number one at
current competitions, got the day off to a bad start, losing 6-1
6-4 to Ludmila Richterova, 19, who had replaced leading Czech
player Jana Novotna, suffering from shingles.
</P>
<P>
Richterova showed her superiorities from the beginning and took
the first five games in a row in just 18 minutes, leaving no room
for Rittner.
</P>
<P>
Rittner pulled back one game but could not change her fate of
failure.
</P>
<P>
Marlene Weingaertner, 17, who pulled off a surprise victory
over Richterova on Saturday, could not keep her momentum on Sunday
and lost 6-2, 6-2 to Adriana Gersi to give the Czechs the
victory. 
</P>
