<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Foreign Trade (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's foreign trade amounted to
289.9 billion US dollars last year, 3.2 percent more than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Exports were valued at 151.07 billion US dollars and imports at
138.83 billion US dollars, increases of 1.5 and 5.1 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
An analysis shows that processing trade reached 146.6 billion
US dollars, which broke down into 84.3 billion US dollars for
exports and 62.3 billion US dollars for imports.
</P>
<P>
China's conventional trade last year was worth 102.2 billion US
dollars, up 14 percent over a year ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
