<HEADLINE> Italy Calls for Restoring Calm in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Referring to the unstable situation
in Albania, Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said today that
the first thing to do is to restore calm in the country and then all
parties "must sit around a table" to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
Dini said on the sidelines of a trade fair that the unstable
situation in Albania, where the government has resigned and street
violence remained unabated, has become a problem for all of Europe.
</P>
<P>
"We would like to see intervention by Europe and international
financial organizations," Dini said.
</P>
<P>
He said that all parties in Albania "must sit around a table
and we will work in this direction." 
</P>
