<HEADLINE> Spain Crash Out of Federation Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Belgium knocked out
pre-tournament favourites Spain in the first round of the
Federation Cup World Group 1 competitions on Sunday in Sprimont,
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Arantxa Sanchez Vicario suffered her second defeat in two days,
giving the Belgians an unbeatable 3-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
The former world number one, already beaten by substitute Els
Callens on Saturday, was beaten 6-3, 2-6, 8-6 by Belgium's leading
player Sabine Appelmans.
</P>
<P>
Belgium will face France in the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez Vicario, current world no.4, who had won her six
previous matches against world number 19 Appelmans, seemed to be
under great pressure during the match.
</P>
<P>
Spain have won the Cup four times in the past six years,
including victories over the United States in 1991, 1994 and 1995.
</P>
<P>
Spain were without Conchita Martinez, who formed with Sanchez
Vicario the most successful doubles combination in Cup history.
Martinez has tendinitis in her right shoulder. 
</P>
