<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Savings Deposits Up (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Savings deposits at China's
banking system increased last year despite two interest rate cuts.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that total personal savings deposits
across the nation had reached more than 3.85 trillion yuan by the
end of 1996, up 30 percent, or 880.5 billion yuan, over a year
before.
</P>
<P>
As their incomes surged along with a rapidly-growing economy,
Chinese people put more of their surplus cash into banks despite
interest rate cuts on May 1 and August 23.  
</P>
</TEXT>
