<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Tour de Langkawi Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Luca Scinto of Italy took the
title of the Le Tour de Langkawi cycling race which ended on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Scinto, pre-race favorite, earned the final yellow jersey and
went on to win the overall individual title after 12 stages of the
1,608.5 kilometers tour.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Scinto crossed the finishing line to take the
tropyh awarded by Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad at
Pulau Langkawi.
</P>
<P>
In the 60.5-kilometer last stage was won by Scinto's teammate
Fabiano Fontanelli who clocked a time of one hour 13 minutes and
50 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Gerardus Kemper of the Netherlands finished second behind
Fontanelli and Andrus Aug Finland came home third.
</P>
<P>
Some 150 riders from 25 teams took part in the tour. 
</P>
