<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ivanisevic Beats Bruguera For Italian Indoor Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Top-seeded Goran Ivanisevic met no
further trouble in beating Sergi Bruguera of Spain 6-2, 6-2 in
Sunday's final in Milan and chalked up the Italian Indoor Tennis
title.
</P>
<P>
It was his second ATP Tour title of the year also his second
victory at the Milan event.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old big-serving Croatian used only 45 minutes to
overpower his opponent at Assago Forum.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic, world No. 5, improved his record to 22-3 this year
and captured his 19th career title relying on his powerful,
precise serve and deep backhand passing shots.
</P>
<P>
Bruguera, 26, playing his first final since the 1996 Atlanta
Olympics, was no threat for the more powerful and inspired
opponent.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Ivanisevic, who had won last year's Milan
final against Swiss Marc Rosset in 58 minutes, got a prize of
128,000 U.S. dollars while Bruguera received 68,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
