<HEADLINE> Andretti Wins Miami IndyCar Motor Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Michael Andretti won the
season-opening IndyCar CART Grand Prix of Miami Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Driving a Swift Ford, Michael Andretti scored the first victory
for a U.S.-manufactured chassis since April of 1983.
</P>
<P>
Andretti, driving for the Newman/Haas team, beat Canadian Paul
Tracy, who was in a Penske Mercedes-Benz, and 1996 series champion
Jimmy Vasser, who drove a Reynard Honda. His margin of victory
was 4.2 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The win came in the first outing ever for the Swift chassis in
the series.
</P>
<P>
It was Andretti's second victory in a car debuting in the CART
series. He also won in a Reynard Ford in Australia in 1994.
</P>
</TEXT>
