<DOCNO> XIE19970303.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lesotho Premier Removed as Ruling Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho's ruling Basotholand
Congress Party (BCP) leader, Prime Minister Ntsu Mokhehle has
been removed as party leader due to a decision taken at a BCP
conference at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
BCP Secretariat announced tonight in Maseru, capital of
Lesotho that Mokhehle's dismissal from the party leadership
resulted from a report by the BCP secretary-general which pointed
out his weakness as party leader.
</P>
<P>
The South African Press Association quoted unidentified BCP
officials as charging that Mokhehle failed to perform his duties
effectively and efficiently.
</P>
<P>
Mokhehle was also accused of failing to attend several
meetings of the National Executive Committee and the BCP Working
Committee.
</P>
<P>
He allegedly attended only one meeting of the BCP Working
Committee since he was elected as party leader.
</P>
<P>
Local observers said Mokhehle's removal as party leader is
likely to plunge the kingdom into a constitutional crisis,
because under Lesotho's constitution, the leader of the majority
party in parliament or the leader of a coalition of political
parties shall form the government.
</P>
<P>
The news about whether Mokhehle will command the support of
the majority BCP in parliament is not immediately available.
</P>
</TEXT>
